Two families are reeling after a husband and wife lost their battle against Covid-19. They died less than a week apart. The woman was a nurse at George Mukhari Academic Hospital. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Two families are reeling after a husband and wife lost their battle against COVID-19. They died less than a week apart. The woman was a nurse at George Mukhari Academic Hospital. Maggy Huma was described as someone who loved her job, on the frontline of the fight against COVID-19. COVID-19: Retired nurses to the rescue Huma lost that battle two weeks ago. Just five days later, her husband Tsitsi too, succumbed to the virus. Both had to be buried immediately. The couple has left behind three children -- a 28-year-old, a 15-year-old and a 10-year-old. The two youngest will now be without a school because they're being forced to relocate. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.